        body: "One of the most powerful formulas in operations:<br><br><strong>L = &lambda; &times; W</strong><br><br>Where:<br>&bull; <strong>L</strong> = average inventory (units in the system)<br>&bull; <strong>&lambda;</strong> = throughput (units per time period)<br>&bull; <strong>W</strong> = average flow time (time a unit spends in system)<br><br>Know any two &rarr; calculate the third! Example: If a café has 10 customers inside (L) and serves 20 customers/hour (&lambda;), the average visit time is W = 10/20 = 0.5 hours = 30 minutes."
